{"id":398,"date":"2024-06-21T11:08:22","date_gmt":"2024-06-21T16:08:22","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/?page_id=398"},"modified":"2025-08-13T11:25:13","modified_gmt":"2025-08-13T16:25:13","slug":"hazing-prevention-team","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/endhazing.sl.ua.edu\/hazing-prevention-team\/","title":{"rendered":"Hazing Prevention Team"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The purpose of the Hazing Prevention Team is to bring campus partners together to address hazing on the University of Louisiana campus, educate the campus community on hazing, and empower the community to take action against hazing. The Hazing Prevention Team seeks to shift campus culture on hazing through prevention, early intervention, and continuous education.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Prevention<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We seek to stop hazing before it happens through ongoing prevention programs which promote the rules and expectations of the University, assist students in making informed decisions, provide alternative methods for growing community, and empower student to hold peers accountable.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Identification and Action<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Being able to identify and act on hazing is important for early intervention. The Hazing Prevention Team\u2019s goal is to equip the campus community with the ability to recognize what hazing looks like from an internal and external perspective. The team provides clearly defined next steps and reporting resources for instances when a community member may suspect hazing is occurring.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Continuous Education<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Hazing Prevention Team seeks to address instances directly in a holistic and meaningful way. When an individual or organization is accused of hazing, the team provides necessary interventions and need-specific, research-based educational programs.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/universityofalabama.az1.qualtrics.com\/jfe\/form\/SV_bmyg05il4SFFKf4\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Hazing Prevention Presentation Request<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Membership<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Membership is comprised of campus partners who support student organizations, who have direct involvement with the hazing investigation process or who are tasked with supporting holistic student well-being.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Chairs<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Hazing Prevention Team is chaired by <a href=\"mailto:cwentworth@ua.edu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Christina Clark<\/a> and <a href=\"mailto:akwallace4@ua.edu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Abby McNeal<\/a>. If you have any questions, please reach out to them. <\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper  \"><div class=\"ua_layout--grid\" >\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\">Christina Clark<\/h2>\n\n<p>Student Conduct Investigator, Student Conduct&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n<\/div><\/article>\n    <\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class=\"ua_card_title\">Abby Wallace McNeal<\/h2>\n\n<p>Assistant Director, Fraternity and Sorority Life<\/p>\n\n<\/div><\/article>\n    <\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Team Members<\/h3>\n\n\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper  alignwide\"><div class=\"ua_layout--grid\" style=--grid-column-count:3>\n<div  >\n<div class=\"ua_component_wrapper \">\n      <article class=\"ua_card\">\n        <div class=\"ua_card_content-wrapper\">\n            <h2 class